On the other hand, Mónika Lamperth, Minister of Labour, does not invite her collaborators officially to a Christmas party but to a work meeting at the end of the year.
One hundred and eighty people are expected to be invited to have a coffee and eat donuts, the press service said, the party will cost only 350,000 forints.
Gordon Bajnai, Minister of Local Government, will simply invite his staff to have a drink in the classroom of the Ministry of Local Government and Territorial Planning.
