They added that the initiative had sparked lively debates in Bulgarian public opinion.
As they say, the statement by some Bulgarian Roma organizations regarding the constitution of their own guard as resistance signals the increased risk of ethnic clashes.
The operation of the Hungarian Guard showing similarities to that of the Bulgarian National Guard does not preclude Hungarian Roma from reacting to the threat in the same way by organizing their own self-defense, Political Capital’s risk warning reads.
At the request of the telegraphic agency, Attila Juhász, research director of Political Capital, said: risk analysis is one of the activities of the research institute.
