Congress approves the transposition of MIFID, which entered into force on 1 November
In parallel with its parliamentary formality, which ended today with the vote of the Congress of amendments incorporated into the draft in the Senate, the Government submitted to a public hearing the regulations that will develop the new law, with the objective of its entry into force before the end of the year.
The representatives of the various groups agreed to highlight the effort made by Members of Parliament and Senators to negotiate and agree on the best regulations to ensure investor protection and to regulate in detail the activities of the agencies so that markets function effectively.
The MIFID, which amends the Securities Market Law, involves the modernization of financial markets, at a time when it strengthens investor protection, improves the powers of the leaders of the National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) and promotes cooperation between the different leaders of the European Union.
The new regulations will provide financial advisory services for specialized social reasons as well as for natural or legal persons and create a new type of financial advisory services (ESIS), financial advisory firms (FIAs), which merge with securities companies, securities agencies and portfolio management companies.
In addition, it increases the number of systems for the execution of transactions on financial instruments, so that it is possible to add to the regulated secondary markets the multilateral trading systems and the systems of internationalization of orders, which compete with the current managers of exchanges.
The Act also obliges investment firms to disclose on the market information on key aspects of their business profile, risk exposure and forms of risk management and it obliges them to keep a record of all transactions they carry out, to facilitate control by the CNMV.
Through the Congressional Economic Commission, several amendments have been added, including one that highlights that securitized debt will be considered a "complex" financial instrument given its high risk to the investor, which has been demonstrated with what happened with the debt of U.S. high-risk mortgages (subprime).
In addition, they took advantage of the transposition of the management took advantage of to legally delimit the functions that graduates in Economics can have 30 years after in 1977, was approved the Royal Decree that delimits the professional functions reserved for economists.
For its part, the Senate has incorporated the creation of new figures in the financial sector, such as the Ombudsman, who will work on behalf of a company, who will not require the authorization of the CNMV and who will be able to provide its services of marketing products and attracting new customers to different investment companies at the same time.
