What insurance is right for me?
Car insurance, which covers the driver in the event of a claim, involves a significant expense that will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, driving licence seniority, marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use made of it, among others.
Having a car is the main thing.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the model of the vehicle.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insurer.
This compromise is materialized by an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the value of the premium granted and in return it becomes responsible for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of a disaster.
The premium is the price of the insurance, which is established by taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, seniority of the driver's license, marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use made of it, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics so that the higher the likelihood of an accident, the higher the odds to pay.
It is for this reason that people over 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, since statistics show that these people have a lower claim rate than their precautions.
Similarly, using censuses, companies concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will affect the frequency, and therefore the likelihood of an accident.
As the frequency increases, the probabilities increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when determining the premium price.
For this reason, the driver must carefully study the situation to choose the car insurance that best suits his profile.
Here we will expose the most significant variables when choosing one or the other type of insurance, so that this, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insurer, offers a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 face a variety of disadvantages when entering into a contract with affordable insurance, such as low driving experience and seniority of the driver's license.
While it is ideal to be well insured to be a full-fledged insurance, other, more economical options exist.
The most foresighted drivers can opt for all-risk insurance with deductible, so that they get the coverage of all-risk insurance but at a more affordable price.
This form of agreement implies that the customer pays part of the amount of the claim.
"The portion of the claim amount that the client pays will be established according to the value of the premium, which will be higher the amount will be lower," specifies Luis Noguera, the head of Spain of First Europa, online insurance broker.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer provides protection to deal with damage caused to third parties, but by for those caused on his own car.
In addition, it would be covered against theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
I'll give you some advice.
If you are under 25 try to be cautious and avoid claims as much as possible, as this will affect the bonus, which may reduce the price of the insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction in the base fare that the company has.
On the contrary, a sanction is an increase in the basic tariff.
"The bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and its profit.
If the company has had a good year it will be able to afford to increase the bonuses ", clarifies Noguera.
After the age of 25, it becomes easier for drivers to sign a contract with insurance, as the claim rate is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
This is why it is best to choose all-risk insurance with deductible.
"Normally, young people cannot take advantage of the experience gained after an accident," said the director of the European company in Spain, adding that the majority of accidents occur during the second year of driving, once the 'fear of the novice' has passed.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is preferable that he negotiates full-risk insurance, as long as his economic situation allows it.
Marriages with children are considered by insurers to be the people with the lowest claims rate, because the increases will be lower.
In this case the best insurance would be a full-risk insurance with deductible (may be 300 euros), or an extended third-party insurance from the third year of life of the vehicle when the insured has a high level of bonus.
“They have a more casual drive and they have greater purchasing power to afford the luxury of taking on a larger amount of franchises,” Noguera said.
For retirees, an all-risk insurance with deductible is preferable (the latter being 150 euros), or an extended third-party insurance when the insurer has a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver in the face of possible claims, but also because it represents a significant expense, which is why it is fundamental to study properly the insurance that suits us most according to our personal situation.
