The CD "Live 1974" that has just been released was recorded during a concert in Griessem in front of a record audience of nearly 50 heads, as someone thinks they remember.
Rother issued at that time the wish to force Harmonia to train from time to time.
This was an immoral requirement for Roedelius and Moebius.
The band announced their separation in 1975.
Rother landed in the spheres of esotericism and secured his existence with albums such as "Flammende Herzen" (hearts in flames).
Cluster revived in the 1980s and has since become more successful than Harmonia has ever been.
We owe Griessem's Live album to Herbert Grönemeyer.
His label Grönland set itself the goal of maintaining Krautrock as a German contribution inherent in contemporary music.
Neu! had already been unearthed on this occasion as the personal work of Roedelius.
The physical resurrection of Harmonia takes place at the House of World Cultures in Berlin.
Publicly subsidized, as part of the Woldtronics Festival.
Julian Cope is here, the British, former punk and author of the paperback book "Krautrock Sampler".
